<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 27 at 5:42AM EST  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Calhoun,
southeastern Van Buren and Kalamazoo Counties through 630 AM EST...
At 541 AM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lawton, or 8 miles southeast of Paw Paw, moving east at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Marshall...
Battle Creek...        Paw Paw...             Vicksburg...
Galesburg...           Mattawan...            Lawton...
Union City...          Schoolcraft...         Climax...
Burlington...          Brownlee Park...       Fulton...
Athens...              Tekonsha...            Oshtemo...
Pine Creek...          Ceresco...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
